name: The double
chatter: The Mariners' Edgar Martinez doubles down the left-field line to score Joey Cora and Ken Griffey Jr. for an AL Division Series-clinching, come-from-behind Game 5 win over the Yankees in the 11th inning at the Kingdome.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/F8SBJzOEcyU" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Largent's revenge
chatter: Seahawks receiver Steve Largent gets his revenge in a big way on Denver safety Mike Harden, who had illegally hit Largent with an elbow to the head in the season opener. In the next meeting, Harden intercepts a pass by QB Dave Krieg. During the return Largent unleashes a vicious blindside hit, slamming Harden to the Kingdome turf and causing a fumble that Largent recovers.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/xSOPrwb-mQc" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: The tip
chatter: Seahawks cornerback Richard Sherman tips a pass intended for Michael Crabtree to linebacker Malcolm Smith in the end zone to end a potential San Francisco 49ers comeback and preserve a 23-17 victory in the NFC Championship Game.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/OhtfaME_v0Y" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Seattle Slew wins Triple Crown
chatter: Undefeated Seattle Slew -- owned by Washington couples Mickey and Karen Taylor and Jim and Sally Hill and named to honor the city and Pacific Northwest logging -- wins the Belmont Stakes and horse racing’s Triple Crown.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/JoRFw7mcQ8c" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: The return
chatter: Percy Harvin returns the second-half opening kickoff in Super Bowl XLVIII for a TD against the Denver Broncos at MetLife Stadium in New Jersey to effectively clinch the Seahawks' first championship.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/3IpNCb7Xfx0" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Sooner Schooner
chatter: After a nullified field goal and “Sooner Schooner’’ incident, the Washington Huskies score two touchdowns in less than a minute to snap a fourth-quarter tie and defeat No. 2 Oklahoma 28-17 in the Orange Bowl.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/BOOFp-Bwkzk" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Beast Quake
chatter: Marshawn Lynch's signature Seahawks moment comes with 3:22 left in a wild-card game against the Saints. On first-and-10 from the Seattle 33-yard line, Lynch gets the carry and takes off, weaving through the Saints' secondary, breaking eight tackles and stiff-arming Tracy Porter en route to a 67-yard touchdown run. The roar of CenturyLink Field's crowd registers on earthquake monitoring stations and thus the Beast Quake is born.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/foD3dkZR3fI" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Whammy in Miami
chatter: The Washington Huskies football team ends Miami's 58-game home winning streak -- a record that still stands -- with a 38-20 victory. After trailing 14-3 at halftime, the Huskies score 35 second-half points, including 22 in a five-minute span. One UW touchdown comes on a fumble recovery by offensive lineman Bob Sapp, who later coins the phrase "Whammy in Miami" in an interview.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/KyunngXlfeM" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Masked Bird
chatter: Sue Bird, wearing a mask after breaking her nose, catches fire and scores 14 of her 22 points in the fourth quarter in Game 5 of the WNBA Western Conference Finals to close out the Mercury and lead the Storm to the WNBA Finals.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/BENa6zdM3XA" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: U.S. Open drama
chatter: Chambers Bay in University Place plays host to one of the most dramatic U.S. Open finishes in recent memory, featuring a final-round showdown between rising stars Jordan Spieth and Dustin Johnson. Spieth wins the tournament after Johnson three-putts on the 18th hole. That comes after golfers had complained about the condition of Chambers Bay greens during the tournament.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/Vpfr-lOqXrY" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Perfection for Felix
chatter: Mariners pitcher Felix Hernandez freezes Sean Rodriguez of the Tampa Bay Rays for his 12th strikeout, sealing a 1-0 victory at Safeco Field and the first perfect game in franchise history. His celebration after the final out -- both arms raised and one leg kicking, later dubbed "Felixing" -- becomes a signature moment of his career.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/43ICt9_W2Y4" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Big Unit, big relief
chatter: Mariners ace Randy Johnson makes a dramatic relief appearance on one day's rest in Game 5 of their American League Division Series against the Yankees at the Kingdome. Entering a 4–4 game in the ninth inning, the American League Cy Young winner pitches the ninth, 10th and 11th innings in the Mariners' victory.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/GlwqoP6_Ghc" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: The save
chatter: Stefan Frei's outstretched arm while leaping instantly becomes the most iconic moment in Sounders history, and "The save" helps lift them to their first MLS Cup trophy. Frei denies what appears to be a go-ahead goal by Toronto FC striker Jozy Altidore in extra time by leaping to the top left corner of the net and swatting the ball away. Seattle goes on to win on penalty kicks.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/igBBNMzsiYA" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Fail Mary
chatter: In the infamous “Fail Mary’’ play on Monday Night Football at CenturyLink Field, a TD bomb by Seahawks quarterback Russell Wilson to Golden Tate delivers a stunning 14-12 win over Green Bay and seals the fate of NFL replacement referees after obvious offensive pass interference was missed.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/cnGa6ycrYYM" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Plum claims record in style
chatter: Kelsey Plum hits a running left-handed jumper against Utah at Alaska Airlines Arena to put the finishing touches on a team-record 57-point game while becoming women's college basketball's career scoring leader, passing Jackie Stiles' record of 3,393 points.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/kzINYC3IoGE" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Four homers for Cammy
chatter: Mike Cameron and his tarred Rawlings bat make baseball history as the Mariners outfielder hits four home runs in a blowout win over the White Sox in Chicago. Cameron, who becomes the 13th player to hit four homers in a major-league game, said: "Today was pretty groovy. ... It was just one of those days."
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/K8oZT2MC51c" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Sonics crowned
chatter: Defensive stopper Dennis Johnson scores 21 points and secures NBA Finals MVP honors as the Sonics defeat the defending-champion Washington Bullets 97-93 in Game 5 of the 1979 NBA Finals at Landover, Maryland, to claim their first title and avenge their loss to the Bullets in the 1978 Finals.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/DJMJgm43f6g" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: The point
chatter: The Washington Huskies football team ends a 12-year losing streak to hated rival Oregon in resounding fashion, routing the Ducks 70-21 in Eugene, Oregon. The highlight of the game comes courtesy of UW quarterback Jake Browning, who points his finger at an Oregon linebacker while scoring the game's first touchdown.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/2fQBub19yJo" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Smelling Roses
chatter: Lineman Steve Emtman leads a smothering Huskies defense to a 34-14 pasting of Michigan in the Rose Bowl to claim a share of the national title with Miami and a second-straight Rose Bowl title. The win puts the exclamation mark on Don James' legendary coaching career at Washington.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/Qh3adBAzuh0" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Storm wins first title
chatter: Betty Lennox scores 16 second-half points as the  Storm defeats Connecticut 74-60 at KeyArena to win the franchise’s first WNBA championship in a decisive third game.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/bqHQLZ1MfXM" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Seahawks' OT comeback
chatter: Former Huskies receiver Jermaine Kearse hauls in a 35-yard TD pass in overtime from Russell Wilson at CenturyLink Field to defeat Green Bay in the greatest comeback in NFC Championship Game history, sending the Seahawks to their second consecutive Super Bowl.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/3yzhblg_uxQ" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Something out of Star Wars
chatter: A's baserunner Terrence Long is halfway to third after a single to right field against the Mariners in Oakland when Ichiro fields the ball and delivers a laser to third baseman David Bell’s glove, which meets Long’s foot before reaching the base. “I’m here to tell you that Ichiro threw something out of Star Wars down there at third base,” Mariners broadcaster Dave Niehaus bellows.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/WYAxk01E404" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Boys in the boat
chatter: The Washington Huskies men's crew – aka “The Boys in the Boat” -- defeats Italy and Germany in the men’s eights to win unexpected gold at the 1936 Olympic Games in Berlin.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/n58w0BctOvs" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Rapinoe strikes a pose
chatter: U.S. star and OL Reign forward Megan Rapinoe triumphantly stretches her arms out, embracing the crowd and the moment after scoring one of her two goals against France during the quarterfinals of the 2019 Women's World Cup in France. Team USA goes on to win the World Cup.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/L6MeWGuldeY" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Sounders taste victory
chatter: Victor Rodriguez's goal gives the Sounders a 2-0 lead vs. Toronto in the MLS Cup final and sets off a wild celebration by the CenturyLink Field crowd. The party continues through the end of the Seattle's 3-1 win, its second MLS Cup title.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/RCeqgU540Xc" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Cold-blooded Thomas
chatter: Washington Huskies star Isaiah Thomas makes a long, buzzer-beating jumper in overtime to beat Arizona 77-75 in the title game of the Pac-10 men's basketball tournament in Los Angeles. Broadcaster Gus Johnson calls the shot "Cold-blooded!" as the buzzer sounds and Thomas pumps his fist.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/y2TtyeXgYM8" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: NHL headed to Seattle
chatter: The NHL approves a proposal by Seattle's ownership group, led by David Bonderman, Jerry Bruckheimer and Tod Leiweke, to grant the city an expansion franchise, which would make Seattle the league's 32nd team. The team -- which is still to be named -- is scheduled to begin play at a renovated KeyArena beginning in 2021.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/SUswvmPyTx4" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Ichiro's hit record
chatter: Ichiro's third-inning single off Rangers right-hander Ryan Drese at Safeco Field gives the Mariners outfielder Major League Baseball's season hits record at 258, breaking George Sisler’s record that had stood for 84 years
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/HL-XjMCPfio" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Stewie powers Storm
chatter: Eventual Finals MVP Breanna Stewart scores a playoff-best 30 points as the Storm crushes the Washington Mystics 98-82 in Landover, Maryland, to sweep the WNBA Finals, clinching the franchise's third title.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/6vAXJElDCxY" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Back-to-back Griffey blasts
chatter: The Mariners' Ken Griffey Sr. and Ken Griffey Jr. become the first father and son to hit back-to-back home runs in a game, taking Angels starter Kirk McCaskill deep during the first inning in Anaheim, California.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/vCk1UY5Afus" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Everybody scores
chatter: The signature moment of the Mariners' one-game playoff against the Angels at the Kingdome comes with two outs in the seventh inning and Seattle clinging to a 1-0 lead. Luis Sojo comes around from first base to score after former Mariner Mark Langston’s wild relay to the plate. “Everybody scores!” was broadcaster Rick Rizzs’ classic call.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/vJ0ftBHJJFs" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>

name: Kemp's Lister blister
chatter: Sonics forward Shawn Kemp takes the art of the disrespectful dunk to another level with a jam over former Sonic Alton Lister in a first-round playoff series against the Warriors. Lister had helped contain the Reign Man over the first few games of the series, but Kemp gets revenge with one of the transcendent dunks in NBA history. For good measure, Kemp stands over Lister and pumps two fingers at him while sprawled on the hardwood.
Video: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/l2GaAWdHwsw" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
